x4freetext: -DIFFERENTIAL GAMMA-RAY PRODUCTION CROSS SECTIONS
MEASURED IN SI(N,XG), CR(N,XG) AND NI(N,XG) REACTIONS
FOR INCIDENT NEUTRONS BETWEEN 3 AND 7 MEV ENERGY, AND
ALSO AT 14.1 MEV-. (IN FRENSH)
ELECTROSTATIC ACCELERATOR FOR THE 14.1 MEV
NEUTRONS.
4 MEV VAN DE GRAAFF FOR THE 3 TO 7 MEV
NEUTRONS.
SOLID TRITIUM TARGET, THICKNESS 0.4 MG/CM2.
DEUTERIUM GAS TARGET, 2 CM LONG WITH A
PRESSURE OF 2 ATM.
.POWDER, NATURAL ABUNDUCE, IN ALUMINUM CONTAINERS,
DISC SHAPED FOR THE 14.1 MEV MEASUREMENTS AND
CYLINDRICAL SHAPED, 3 CM DIA. AND 5 CM LENGTH, FOR
THE 3 TO 7 MEV MEASUREMENTS.
TIME OF FLIGHT TECHNIQUES.
AN EFFICIENCY CALIBRATED GE(LI) DETECTOR
80 CM3 IN AN ANTI-COMPTON ARRANGMENT WITH A NAI(TL)
DETECTOR.
USED AS ANTI-COMPTON DETECTOR WITH THE GE(LI)
DETECTOR.
NE102 PLASTIC SCINTILLATOR, EFFICIENCY
CALIBRATED AGAINST A LONG COUNTER, TO MEASURE THE
NEUTRON FLUX BETWEEN 3 AND 7 MEV.
.DATA TAKEN FROM MAIN REFERENCE.
CN.
.CORRECTIONS FOR NEUTRON ATTENUATION AND GAMMA-RAY
SELF-ABSORBTION IN THE SAMPLE HAVE BEEN APPLIED.
.THE FOLLOWING UNCERTAINTIES ARE GIVEN,
- 6 TO 50 PERCENT FOR INTEGRATION OF GAMMA-RAY LINES
- 5 PERCENT FOR GAMMA-RAY DETECTION EFFICIENCY
- 5 PERCENT FOR THE NEUTRON FLUX MEASUREMENT AT 14.1
MEV
- 12 PERCENT FOR THE NEUTRON FLUX MEASUREMENT AT 3
TO 7 MEV
- 2 PERCENT FOR THE GAMMA CORRECTION FACTOR
- 1 PERCENT FOR THE NEUTRON CORRECTION FACTOR.
GAMMA-RAY ENERGY FROM PRODUCT NUCLIDE AL-28.
.DATA TAKEN FROM TABLE II IN MAIN REFERENCE.
